<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Close the unit, and look back across the whole year's design thread.</p>
  <p>The unit closes with self-assessment against the success criteria and a look back across the year-long design thread. You named and quantified trade-offs in a Chennai neighbourhood the way you weighed competing stakeholders over water in Unit 5, defended recommendations to a planning audience in Unit 4, and read a landscape in Unit 2. The move that ran through all of it: real design has no win-everything answer, and honest work names what it gave up. Unit 7 takes that same trade-off reasoning to energy.</p>
  <p>Self-assessment here is not busywork. Reading your own plan against the rubric, before a grade is attached, is how you learn to see the gap between what you meant and what a reader actually gets. The students who do this honestly are the ones who get better fastest, because they stop being surprised by their feedback.</p>
</section>

