<section class="block-section concepts" style="margin-top:24px;">
  <span class="section-tag">🔭 Preview — Unit 7</span>
  <h2>Where we go next</h2>
  <p>Unit 7 (Energy &amp; Sustainability) takes the same design reasoning to a new system: how a city or region should power itself. You will weigh cost, emissions, land use, reliability, and equity in an energy mix, and argue for it in public, much as you argued for a neighbourhood here. The trade-off move you practised on land carries straight across to energy, and Unit 7 closes the year.</p>
  <p>The frameworks from this unit (multi-objective optimisation, naming and quantifying trade-offs, AI Documentation, designing for a real public audience) do not get retaught in Unit 7. They get used. If something feels shaky, the <a href="/foundations/">Foundations</a> pages stay live all year.</p>
</section>
